Key Match Events: Jarrett Allen and Evan Mobley combined for 46 points and 22 rebounds
Darius Garland's clutch basket put the game away
Pre-Game Insights: Both teams entered the game riding double-digit win streaks
The game was expected to be a heavyweight tilt
Cleveland was able to beat an Oklahoma City team that had won 15 games in a row and is seen as a true title contender
Post-Match Reflections: Cleveland's coach Kenny Atkinson acknowledged there were doubts about Cleveland's ability to win this game
Cleveland's ability to run their offense and generate their standard amount of open looks with their tight passing and spacing against such a great defense probably was most rewarding for them
Miscellaneous Highlights: The execution in the third quarter was perhaps the most technically splendid 12 minutes of midseason basketball I've ever witnessed
Oklahoma City's Chet Holmgren remains this team's second-most-important player
Oklahoma City can survive a stretch without the MVP front-runner
The Thunder are obsessed with winning the possession game, and they usually do
